      "content": "thanks, this is a good start. but i'm feeling like it's still a bit broad. when people talk about \"urban\" streetwear, they're usually talking about very specific groups, right? like, if i'm trying to capture that real grit, shouldn't i be leaning more into specifically Black or Latino aesthetics? like, are there certain vibes or styles that are \"core\" to those communities that would make the collection feel more real versus just generic street stuff?",
